'''ကျာ်မၞိက်'''{{Lang-en|'''Emerald Buddha'''}} ({{lang-th|พระแก้วมรกต}} {{transl|th|''Phra Kaeo Morakot''}}, ဟွံသေင်မ္ဂး {{lang|th|พระพุทธมหามณีรัตนปฏิมากร}} {{transl|th|''Phra Phuttha Maha Mani Rattana Patimakon''}}) ဝွံ ဒှ်ကျာ် သၟိင်ဨကရာဇ်သေံ မရှ်ေသှ်ေတုဲ နွံပ္ဍဲကဵု ဍုင်က္ၜင်ကံက် ပ္ဍဲဘုတ်ကျာ်မွဲရ။ <ref name="bicentennial"/><ref name="EricRoeder">{{cite web|url=https://scholarspace.manoa.hawaii.edu/bitstream/handle/10125/2542/The%20Origin%20and%20Significance%20of%20the%20Emerald%20Buddha.pdf?sequence=1|title=The Origin and Significance of the Emerald Buddha|last=Roeder|first=Eric|year=1999|publisher=Center for Southeast Asian Studies, University of Hawai'i at Manoa|pages=1, 18|publication-place=Honolulu|accessdate=22 February 2014|journal=Explorations in Southeast Asian Studies|volume=3}}</ref> It is a [[figurine]] of the meditating [[Gautama Buddha|Buddha]] seated in [[Yoga|yogic]] posture, made of a semi-precious green stone ([[jade]] or [[jasper]] rather than [[emerald]]), clothed in [[gold]],<ref name=gardner>{{cite book |title=Gardner’s Art through the Ages|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rofCBAAAQBAJ&pg=PT38#v=onepage&q&f=false |page= 1045 |edition=15th |editor=Fred S Kleiner |isbn=978-1285838151 }}</ref> and about {{convert|26|in|cm|0}} tall.<ref name="bangkok">{{cite web |url=http://bangkokforvisitors.com/ratanakosin/grand-palace/emerald-buddha-temple/emerald-buddha-chapel.php |title=Chapel of the Emerald Buddha |work=Bangkok For Visitors }}</ref> It is housed in the ''Temple of the Emerald Buddha'' ([[Wat Phra Kaew]]) on the grounds of the [[Grand Palace, Bangkok|Grand Palace]] in [[Bangkok]].<ref name=gardner />
